[1] Tonga (Tongatapu)
Date: Thu 15 Mar 2012
Source: Radio New Zealand International [edited]
http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=66856


There are 2 confirmed cases of typhoid in Tongatapu: the first cases of 2012. Radio Tonga reports a teenage boy and a 5-year old child from Tatakamotonga are in Vaiola hospital getting specialist treatment for typhoid.

Dr. Malakai 'Ake of Vaiola Hospital says it is likely that the patients contracted the bacterium because of poor hygiene.
The two current typhoid cases lead doctors to believe that there are still people in Tongatapu who are carrying the bacterium, but are healthy and don't appear infectious.

The Ministry of Health has banned communal feasting. They will also test the family and friends of the patients.

