[2] Fiji (Viti Levu)
Date: Wed 14 Mar 2012
Source: Fiji Times [edited]
http://www.fijitimes.com/story.aspx?id=195955


A total of 15 cases of typhoid have been confirmed at Koroboya Village in Ba and nearby settlements. This was confirmed by Ministry of Health officials who have been living at the village ever since a public health emergency regulation was imposed in Feb 2012. According to Ba sub-divisional medical officer Dr Luse Tinakoi, the 15 people were from Koroboya Village, nearby Naitarisi Village and people living in settlements outside the village.

While updating the Commissioner Western Commander Joeli Cawaki, Dr Luse said their operations to contain the outbreak were welcomed by the villagers. "The villagers know that they were the cause of the outbreak and we believe that the compliance of the villagers to our regimen is 100 percent," Dr Luse said.

[Byline: Repeka Nasiko]

